We went to this restaurant at Westshore Plaza last night to celebrate St. Patrick's Day.  My husband said our waitress had an attitude, but I didn't think much about it then.  Our 6-year-old left his rabbit toy at the restaurant.  As soon as we realized it, we called to make sure the restaurant kept it.  Today we drove there to pick it up.  I explained myself to a waitress and asked her for the rabbit.  She completely ignored me.  Our waitress from last night was standing next to me, but I couldn't even get to talk to her because she looked past me.  After standing near the bar/kitchen door where waitresses just walked past me for about 15 minutes, I left.  I went back to the car and told my husband what happened.  My husband went to the restaurant and received the same treatment.  He was also ignored by our waitress from last night.  Finally he decided to stand in the middle of the kitchen door to get someone's attention.  He asked for the manager, and was told that the manager was too busy to meet him.  After some argument, finally he got the rabbit.  All the time our waitress stood near the door and pretended not to hear or see anything.  So much trouble for trying to get our son's rabbit toy!  We don't deserve to be treated like this.  We work hard for our money and we regret giving our waitress a tip.  If we knew she would treat us badly the next day, we wouldn't have tipped her at all.  We won't return to this restaurant.
